Complete Process for New Users

  A new user needs to do these steps:

  1. If patching to a current build, ensure GROMACS is already installed. If not, change the make command in step 4 from -DGROMACS_ROOT=/path/to/gromacs to -DGROMACS=2024.4 or whichever version you want. 

  2. Get SSAGES Source Code (if they don't have it)

  git clone https://github.com/SSAGESproject/SSAGES.git
  cd SSAGES

  3. Apply the Modern GROMACS Patch

  # Copy the patch files to SSAGES directory
  cp /path/to/patch/files/* .

  # Run the installer (this applies the patch)
  ./install-modern-gromacs-support.sh

  4. Build SSAGES with Modern GROMACS

  mkdir build && cd build
  cmake .. -DGROMACS=ON -DUSE_EXTERNAL_GROMACS=ON -DGROMACS_ROOT=/path/to/gromacs
  make -j$(nproc)
